---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="AI Governance – Onyx Labs"
  description="Operationalize AI governance without slowing teams down."
>
  <section class="content-main">
    <div class="container shell">
      <div class="content-layout">
        <div>
          <div class="content-kicker">AI Governance</div>
          <h1 class="content-heading">Operationalize AI governance without slowing teams down.</h1>
          <p class="content-lede">
            We help you translate high-level AI principles into concrete controls, workflows, and
            approval paths that product, data, and legal teams can all live with.
          </p>
          <div class="content-tags">
            <span class="tag">Risk & Compliance</span>
            <span class="tag">Model Governance</span>
            <span class="tag">LLM Policy Design</span>
            <span class="tag">Regulatory Readiness</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside class="content-panel">
          <h3>Where we typically start</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Map current and planned AI use-cases to risk categories.</li>
            <li>Define review workflows and approval lanes per risk tier.</li>
            <li>Create lightweight documentation and decision templates.</li>
            <li>Design evaluation and red-teaming strategies per use-case.</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>AI policy and control design</h3>
          <p>
            We work with your legal, risk, and security teams to draft AI policies that are both
            defensible and implementable, then partner with product and engineering to turn them
            into real controls.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Policy frameworks aligned with upcoming regulations.</li>
            <li>Model and data access controls tuned to your stack.</li>
            <li>Guardrail patterns covering safety, misuse, and abuse.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>Governance that product can work with</h3>
          <p>
            Governance only works when your product teams can move. We design review workflows that
            are fast for low-risk changes and appropriately deep for sensitive launches.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Risk-tiered review checklists and playbooks.</li>
            <li>Launch gates tied to evaluation results and sign-offs.</li>
            <li>Post-incident review patterns for AI-specific failures.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-section">
        <div class="section-header flex justify-between align-items-start flex-wrap gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <div class="section-title">Example outcomes</div>
            <p class="section-subtitle mb-0">
              You leave with a living governance system, not a static slide deck.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Playbooks</div>
            <div class="card-title">AI use-case catalog & risk tiers</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Central inventory of AI use-cases with clearly documented risk levels, controls, and
              owners.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Controls</div>
            <div class="card-title">Evaluation & monitoring standards</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Standardized expectations for testing, red-teaming, and monitoring before and after
              launch.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Enablement</div>
            <div class="card-title">Governance training for builders</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Training for PMs, designers, and engineers on how to ship inside your governance
              model.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
